On **.NET 10 SDK**, you get native MTP integration via `global.json` — no `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` needed. That property is only for .NET 9 and earlier.

**Setup — add a `test` section to `global.json`:**

```json
{
  "sdk": {
    "version": "10.0.100"
  },
  "test": {
    "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform"
  }
}
```

**Key differences from .NET 9:**

| .NET 9 (old) | .NET 10 (new) |
|---|---|
| `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in props | `"test": { "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform" }` in `global.json` |
| MTP args require `--` separator: `dotnet test -- --report-trx` | Args passed directly: `dotnet test --report-trx` |

You still need the framework-specific runner enablement (`EnableMSTestRunner`, `EnableNUnitRunner`, etc.) and `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` — those are unchanged. The `global.json` setting only controls how `dotnet test` communicates with MTP.

